<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading"><span dir="auto">Sinovoip Banana Pi M2+</span></h1>
 
 
<div id="bodyContent">
 
<div id="siteSub">From linux-sunxi.org</div>
 
 
<div id="contentSub"></div>
 
 
<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
Jump to: <a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, <a href="#p-search">search</a>
</div>
 
 
<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>Banana Pi M2+ is <a href="/H3" title="H3">H3</a> based development board produced by <a href="/index.php?title=Sinovoip&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Sinovoip (page does not exist)">Sinovoip</a>.
</p><p><b>Despite its name the M2+ is incompatible to both Banana Pi/M1/M1+/Pro and version <a href="/Sinovoip_Banana_Pi_M2" title="Sinovoip Banana Pi M2">M2</a>, due to a different SoC - requiring different boot loaders and drivers.</b> It's another attempt to cash in on the Banana Pi's popularity with a SBC only sharing brand, name, <strike>form factor</strike> and GPIO header. Fortunately this board is 99% compatible to the H3 Orange Pis, therefore support for it is progressing nicely.
</p>
<table class="infobox" cellspacing="5" style="width:22em;">
